just_use main.go

# label: EARLY
# role: tool — language-aware batch directory / module mover

Batch package / module mover. Reads a `REORG`-style script of
move lines and executes them language-aware: rewrites imports
and module declarations, then moves the directories.

## Status

Graduated from VESTIGIAL → EARLY on 2026-04-21 when the tool was
extended to handle Elm moves. Was built for the 2026-early Go
reorg (relocating lynrummy/ and critters/ under games/). Now
carries two verbs and has been exercised in anger for both Go
and Elm renames.

## Usage

```
# Dry-run (default):
go run cmd/reorg/main.go SCRIPT

# Apply for real:
go run cmd/reorg/main.go --execute SCRIPT
```

Script grammar:

```
# Comments and blank lines ignored.

# Go move: rewrites import paths + package declarations
# across every .go file in the repo.
mv auth/ core/auth/

# Elm move: rewrites `module X` + qualified `X.Y` references
# across every .elm and .claude file under the Elm project.
elm-mv games/lynrummy/elm/src/LynRummy/ games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/
```

## Go semantics (`mv`)

Needs a `go.mod` in the repo root (inferred module path).

- For each move, scans every `.go` file for quoted imports matching
  the old package path or any sub-package and records rewrites.
- If the directory basename changed (e.g. `auth/ → core/newauth/`),
  records `package X` → `package Y` rewrites for files in the
  moved subtree.
- On `--execute`: rewrites imports, moves directories, rewrites
  package declarations, runs `go build ./...` to verify.

## Elm semantics (`elm-mv`)

No `go.mod` needed. The tool auto-detects the Elm project root by
walking upward from the src path looking for `elm.json`.

Source-directory detection:

- Reads `source-directories` from `elm.json` (defaults to `src`).
- Also treats `tests/` as a source-dir by elm-test convention,
  if the directory exists.

Old/new module prefix derivation:

- Takes the path relative to the Elm source-dir and converts `/`
  to `.`. So `src/LynRummy` → `LynRummy`; `src/Game/Tricks` →
  `Game.Tricks`.
- Both src and dst must live under the same Elm project, and
  the computed prefixes must differ.

Rewrite rules:

- Scans every `.elm` and `.claude` file under the project root
  (sidecars use module-qualified names the same as code).
- Regex: `\b<oldPrefix>(\.\*|\.UpperCase[.Chain]*\b)` — matches
  `OldPrefix.Card`, `OldPrefix.Tricks.Hint`, and `OldPrefix.*`
  (the wildcard shorthand common in sidecars).
- Bare `<oldPrefix>` without `.` follow-up (e.g. the word
  "LynRummy" in prose) is NOT rewritten. Prose references to
  the game's name survive.

Dedup: when multiple Elm moves share a (root, oldPrefix,
newPrefix) combo — e.g. `src/LynRummy → src/Game` paired with
`tests/LynRummy → tests/Game` — the tool scans each unique combo
once instead of producing duplicate rewrite rows.

Verification: after executing, runs `./node_modules/.bin/elm
make src/Main.elm --output=/dev/null` in the project root
(falls back to `elm` on `$PATH` if no pinned local install).

## What the tool does NOT do

- Does NOT update references from outside the Elm project (Go
  source comments mentioning `elm/src/LynRummy/X`, Python doc
  strings, READMEs). Those are usually doc paths, not code
  imports, and get high-false-positive risk if auto-rewritten.
  Use `grep + sed` for the post-move sweep, reviewing each hit.
- Does NOT update `cmd/fixturegen` or any other code generator
  that emits Elm module references in string templates. Update
  those by hand before re-running the generator.
- Does NOT handle single-file Elm renames (e.g. renaming
  `Game/Game.elm` to `Game/Turn.elm` which would only change
  one module name's last segment). That would need a different
  verb — not built.

## Pointers

- Entry point: `main.main()`.
- REORG script format documented in the `main.go` header comment.
- The tool was exercised on 2026-04-21 for the `LynRummy → Game`
  rename under games/lynrummy/elm/.
